hopobject.body: Will I get paid for overtime? pharmeducation.ca Scuba divers have discovered an underwater forest in the Gulf of Mexico about 10 miles off the coast of Mobile, AL. It's called the Bald Cyprus Forest. It was buried in 60 feet of water under ocean sediments and protected in an oxygen free environment for more than 50,000 years, until Hurricane Katrina and hurricanes following. This underwater world has drawn the attention of researchers, including one assistant professor at Southern Miss in Hattiesburg.
